<message><from> edu </from><subject><text_normal> ^ [  ame ] mead - multidocument summarization environment </text_normal></subject><to> uib.no </to><date> tue, 26 nov 2002 22:37:23 -0500 (est) </date><content-type> text/plain; charset=us-ascii </content-type><message_body><text_normal> ^ mead  ame released ^  ebsite ^  ame is a multi-document summarization system with multi-lingual capabilities . ^ the  ame system implements extractive summarization , whereby summaries are produced by selecting a subset of highly relevant sentences from the cluster 's overall set of sentences . ^  ame can summarize clusters of english documents on most posix-conforming operating systems and can summarize clusters of  ame chinese documents on a subset of these operating systems . ^ the  ame system has been under development since  um . ^ versions  um and  um were developed at the university of  ame . ^ version  um was developed at a six-week workshop at the  ame  ame university . ^ versions  um through  um were incremental improvements by the  ame workshop team members . ^ with version  um , development of  ame has moved back to the university of  ame . ^ mead  um represents a major refactoring of previous  ame versions . ^ the current version supports all the functionality of previous versions , but also has many new features . ^ some of these are : ^ - version  um is much more configurable than previous versions of  ame . ^ it allows for both system-wide and user-specific configuration files . ^ - it has a simplified user interface . ^ previous versions required the user to manually edit a mead.config file and use a combination of  ame shell commands to produce summaries . ^ while the current version still supports this interface , mead  um has a single script interface that essentially eliminates the need for manual editing of mead.config files . ^ -  ame  ame , a previously free-standing tool for evaluating summarizers , has been incorporated with the current version of  ame . ^ this allows users to evaluate existing summaizers , as well as evaluate the performance of the base mead system and any user modifications . ^ mead  ame supports co-selection ( percent agreement , precision , recall ,  ame ) and content-based evaluation metrics ( such as word overlap and longest common subsequence ) , as well as relative utility . ^ -  ame uses an extensive collection of custom  ame modules that may be suitable for use in many natural language applications , including for example , question answering . ^ -  ame and lead-based summarizers have been incorporated into the  ame framework . ^ these summarizers provide useful examples of how to create new  ame modules . ^ - the documentation for the current version has been expanded , and now includes a significant number of example use cases and tutorials for customizing each of  ame 's modules . ^ to download  ame , including documentation , and view online docs , visit :  ebsite ^ people who have worked on  ame include : ^  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame ,  ame  ame </text_normal></message_body></message>